To: Todd Hammond <todd.hammond@steelx.com.au>
Cc: Mark Purvis <mark.purvis@steelx.com.au>
Subject: Job No. WSS223212,13,14 &15

Hi Todd and Mark,

As discussed earlier today, Phill Gale emailed me regarding changing from zinc to colorbond on all four sheds and I emailed back saying yes, we would change to Deed Ocean and my email has been logged in Job No. WSS223212 so I thought it was all good.
Krysta has now told me that is not all good and all sheds are zinc.
I have called Brad at Metroll in Townsville and he has told me the none of the cladding or flashing has been rolled so I asked him to hold that job until I sort it out.
I have already ordered all the screws required for the for sheds from my supplier in Townsville and I will swap them out when the shed arrive.
Can you please have the cladding changed to Deep Ocean for me.

See email from Phill and my response in the notes in Job No. WSS223212

Peter phoned: following up email. Explained that he is able to provide confirmation email detail, we are unable to change our position.  Builds will go ahead as Zincalume. Peter said this cannot be - clients advised getting colourbond. He wanted to speak to Phil G.  Advised that I am unable to put through to Phil G. I will speak again with Mgt and respond.

**Historical Email from 24/08/2022**
From: peter@palmcoengineering.com <peter@palmcoengineering.com>
Sent: Wednesday, 24 August 2022 5:03 PM
To: Krysta Eichmann <krysta.eichmann@steelx.com.au>
Subject: WSS223212, 13, 14 & 15
 
Hi Krysta,
 
Can’t find any confirmation email, but I remember looking in the job details and seeing my confirmation email in there, so I thought it was confirmed.
See email from Phill, he does have his mobile number at the bottom, but it doesn’t say to call him to confirm.
We are always told to email back with any info so there is a record of the discussion.
I didn’t realise it was a no reply email.
 This is not my mistake it needs to be Ocean Blue C’Bond, the client is expecting C’Bond.
 
Hi Peter
 
There is a quirk in the pricing of BlueScope steel at the moment where the price of Zincalume is now nearly the same as Colorbond. 
 
Did you want to change these 4 buildings to colorbond ? there is no cost to do this.
 
Can you come back to me by the 6th, otherwise will will progress with Zincalume.
 
Phill 0407445547 
Regards,
Phill Gale
